headlines.description: — Joel Embiid had 23 points and nine rebounds, Ben Simmons scored 15 points and the Philadelphia 76ers beat the Dallas Mavericks 111-97 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: All-Stars Embiid, Simmons lead 76ers past Dallas 111-97

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving had 27 points and nine assists, James Harden scored 20 points and the Nets extended their longest winning streak since moving to Brooklyn to eight games with a 129-92 rout of the Orlando Magic on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets rout Magic 129-92, run NBA-leading win streak to eight

events.name: Sacramento Kings at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Immanuel Quickley scored 18 of his 25 points in the first half, and Julius Randle had 21 points and 14 rebounds to power the New York Knicks to a 140-121 win over the Sacramento Kings on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Quickley, Randle lead Knicks to 140-121 rout of Kings

headlines.description: — Tyus Jones scored a career-high 20 points, the Memphis defense held Kawhi Leonard and Paul George to sub-standard nights and the Grizzlies beat the Los Angeles Clipper 122-94 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tyus Jones, defense lead Grizzlies past Clippers, 122-94

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 33 points and the Washington Wizards escaped Denver with a 112-110 victory Thursday night when Facundo Campazzo missed a hurried 3-pointer at the buzzer.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal scores 33, Wizards hang on late to beat Nuggets 112-110

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo scored 38 points, Khris Middleton added 31 and the Milwaukee Bucks outlasted the New Orleans Pelicans 129-125 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 38 as Bucks outlast Pelicans 129-125
